reviewText: funny little independent, with Howard Stern, the voice of Jackie "The Joke Man" Martling, and Bob Nelson as Eppy Epperman, one of his stand up comedy characters. Worth a look for the Howard Stern scenes.
The movie stunk but that is what made it great! Anything with Howard Stern is great to me!!!
Great movie if you have brain damage

How this waste of time and talent survived long enough to get released on DVD is a complete mystery to me.  Enjoyed Bob Nelson in "BRain Donors", but this was poorly conceived, poorly written, poorly directed, and woodenly acted.  Yikes!
